         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">No 53/78 ¶ Colonial Architects Office ¶ Melbourne 5th May 1853 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to enclose for the consideration of His Excellency the Lieutenant Governor a copy of a Letter received from M...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M53.05.05<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Henry Ginn to William Lonsdale</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">B53/4503, unit 185, VPRS 1189 inward registered correspondence, VA 856 Colonial Secretary's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Transcribed 4.9.92. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also J. Duerdin to Botanic Gardens Committee, 2 May 1853, and J. Balmain to J. Foster, 14 September 1853.</p>
               </note>No 53/78</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Colonial Architects Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne 5th May 1853</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to enclose for the consideration of His Excellency the Lieutenant Governor a copy of a Letter received from Mr Jno Duerdin offering for sale, two Green Houses which have lately arrived from England per the "Cherusker".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 29 April 1853, recorded the arrival of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Cherusker</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from London.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With reference to the same I have the honor to state that I have inspected the designs for these Houses and am of opinion that if erected they would be a very great ornament as well as a useful addition to the Gardens and from the Invoices which I have also seen I believe the price to be only the actual cost.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg therefore to Suggest that these Green Houses be purchased for erection in the Gardens the amount requisite for such purchase to be provided by Supplementary Estimates for 1853</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Requesting the favor of your early reply.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Ginn</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hon Sec Botanic Gardens</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honorable The Colonial Secretary</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="4"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="5"/>&amp;c<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 23 May 1853 La Trobe stated: 'I regret that I cannot feel justified in incurring the expense'. He then asked 'what is the cost' and was told, 'Mr Duerdins letter states some where about £600'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by unknown: 'the garden Committee never meet now or I would have referred [...] to them'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.1666in; text-indent: -0.1666in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 11 May La Trobe asked: 'Is it deemed probably that the Leg. Council would sanction the step?' The matter was referred to the Auditor General and G. Rusden, Acting Auditor General, reported: 'There is no provision at present in the absence of the Auditor General the tone of the Legislature, when a proposal for a vote is made to it can scarcely perhaps be commented upon: more especially as a new element of nearly the same number of elected members as the house has [...] next session'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
